Flames shot from Thassalin's mouth as the huge Thraki set a specific piece of forest in Band and then circled over it to detect movements. Strangely, the eerie screeching behind him stopped as he slowed down. Thassalin had forgotten the passengers on his back.
"What's going on, Tenuk, you've already turned into a Thraki before!"
"Flying myself is completely different from being suddenly lifted up by a huge pink dragon!"
"It wasn't that bad, was it, Kayel?"
Kayel was clearly not Nyssi's opinion. He looked less black than usual and his claws had dug so deeply into Thassalin's back that the Thraki was bleeding. Thassalin apparently didn't mind that. Nevertheless, he had realized that he had scared his new friends and landed on a clearing.
„I'm sorry, but I smelled something. So I had to take care of it!“
„But did you have to drag us along too?“, growled Tenuk as he climbed down from Thassalin's back and slid down onto its tail. „And we left Retvik behind! Our big, strong fighter was left behind! How is he supposed to catch up with us?“
„He'll think of something…“, growled Nyssi. „Retvik isn't the fastest, but he's not stupid.“
„Yes, but can Retvik ride?“
Nyssi winked and turned back to Tenuk. „Of course he can ride.“
“Have you ever seen Retvik drive a vehicle? He doesn't have a truck like you, and I haven't seen him drive a nice little car like Kayel's. Besides, he only started using the car for work because you always drive us. He only has his bicycle.”
Laughter broke out as they were interrupted. Thassalin suddenly seemed to find something utterly ridiculous, but no one knew what he was laughing about. It took a bit too long for Thassalin to calm down.
“I'VE BEEN SORRY, BUT I HAD IMAGINED YOUR HUGE FRIEND IN ARMOR ON SUCH A TINY SMALL BIKE FOR TEMTHAN-KIDS. THAT WAS LAUGHABLE! I WISH I HAD SOME KIND OF TELEPATHY. A BEAUTIFUL IMAGINATION! ONE I CANNOT SHARE!”
Kayel chuckled, as he could tell what was going through Thassalin's mind. “Yes, that's true. But what did you smell, and why did you suddenly take off?”
Thassalin grunted, took off and disappeared. When he returned shortly afterwards, he threw something lifeless at Nyssi's feet. It was an Orothrack, a very rare, silver-white dragon creature. But it was missing its head. “ANOTHER DEAD ONE. I HEAR THEIR SHOUTS. SMELL THEIR BLOOD. SOMETHING DRIVES ME TO PROTECT AND HUNT. AS YISINI ORDERS. THEY ARE VERY CLOSE.”
Der mächtige Thraki erstarrte plötzlich. Nyssi und Kayel erstarrten ebenfalls und schauten aufmerksam zu einer Lücke in der Lichtung. Etwas Großes und Schwarzes starrte sie an und fauchte. Was es auch war, es breitete zwei riesige Flügelpaare aus und schoss auf Thassalin zu, ohne sich um die drei kleineren Wesen zwischen ihnen zu scheren. Kayel und Tenuk konnten gerade noch in Deckung gehen, aber Nyssi wurde mitgerissen und fast auf Thassalin geschleudert.
Thassalin reagierte auf diesen Angriff, indem er sich Nyssi schnappte und ihn mit seinem unglaublich langen, geschickten Schwanz auf seinen Rücken schleuderte, bevor er sich selbst in die Luft schwang. Das schwarze, doppelflüglige Wesen verfolgte sie mit hoher Geschwindigkeit.
Kayel schnalzte verärgert, während er sein Gewehr vom Rücken nahm und einen Beutel öffnete, der einen Munitionsgürtel enthielt. Er hängte sich den Gürtel über die Brust, merkte aber rasch, dass Nyssi, der Thraki und das Monster außer Sichtweite waren.
„Hey, Tenuk, könntest du dich in etwas verwandeln, was fliegen kann?“, fragte Kayel.
„Du möchtest sie verfolgen?“
„Yes, of course!“
„But… one of them is a huge monster!“
„Yes and what? I'm standing here with a high-quality rifle in my hand and could start shooting right away. But, well, how should I say – I would have to see it first in order to hit it.“
Tenuk hesitated, then stepped back to make more space. With a quiet, pained grunt, Tenuk's body stretched out, his fur turned into scales and his arms into wings. He quickly transformed into a normal, bright blue Thraki, but his eyes remained red.
„Get on.“
Like an ordinary-looking Thracian, Tenuk now had a proper scaly shield running along his back. Practically speaking, he also had a pair of spines on his back, on which Kayel could hold on. It took a little too long for Tenuk to manage the takeoff, but once in the air, he oriented himself quickly and tried to resume the pursuit.
Tenuk and Kayel quickly realized they were not alone. A second dark creature shot up beneath them, and Tenuk barely avoided a collision.
"That must be the other terrifying giant monster that Lanex was afraid of?" Kayel frowned. He tried to shoot at the second beast, missed, and hastily reloaded.
Tenuk did not answer. He was too focused on the flight toward Nyssi and Thassalin, although the other creature was pursuing them. Kayel turned awkwardly to keep the monster in sight. For Kayel, the fact that it was following them was an advantage, as it made it easier for him to aim and fire. Two shots went through the upper wings of the beast. It screamed in pain and fell back under the trees. Kayel wasn't sure if it was still following them, but it would certainly not be able to keep up with them.
A good distance ahead, Nyssi was desperately clinging on, while Thassalin swung around and spewed fire at the charred monster. The creature was definitely injured. It seemed extremely furious, but not ready to give up. The fireballs seemed to have no desired effect. When Thassalin stretched out, Nyssi used the opportunity to draw her own weapon, an old-fashioned shotgun. It wasn't necessarily the first choice, but maybe the shotguns would scare off the black beast.
